[
  {
    "text": " ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10236/?time=2"
  },
  {
    "text": "Hi, my name is David, and I'm an engineer ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10236/?time=9"
  },
  {
    "text": "on the Documentation Tools team here at Apple. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10236/?time=12"
  },
  {
    "text": "In this session, you'll learn about ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10236/?time=16"
  },
  {
    "text": "hosting DocC documentation ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10236/?time=18"
  },
  {
    "text": "and automating documentation builds. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10236/?time=20"
  },
  {
    "text": "First, I'll talk about building documentation in Xcode ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10236/?time=24"
  },
  {
    "text": "and how you can host ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10236/?time=28"
  },
  {
    "text": "the built documentation archives on a server. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10236/?time=29"
  },
  {
    "text": "Next, I'll go into more detail ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10236/?time=32"
  },
  {
    "text": "of how documentation builds work ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10236/?time=34"
  },
  {
    "text": "and how you can automate building documentation.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10236/?time=36"
  },
  {
    "text": "Throughout this talk, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10236/?time=41"
  },
  {
    "text": "I'll be showing you SlothCreator, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10236/?time=42"
  },
  {
    "text": "a project that my colleagues and I have been working on. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10236/?time=44"
  },
  {
    "text": "We made a website to help people get started. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10236/?time=48"
  },
  {
    "text": "And now, we're really excited about using ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10236/?time=51"
  },
  {
    "text": "the new documentation features in Xcode ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10236/?time=53"
  },
  {
    "text": "to build a version of our documentation ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10236/?time=55"
  },
  {
    "text": "that we can host right on our website. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10236/?time=57"
  },
  {
    "text": "That's going to make it even easier ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10236/?time=60"
  },
  {
    "text": "for people to get started. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10236/?time=61"
  },
  {
    "text": "So let's look at how we can accomplish that.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10236/?time=63"
  },
  {
    "text": "The new documentation features ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10236/?time=68"
  },
  {
    "text": "in Xcode 13 makes it really easy ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10236/?time=69"
  },
  {
    "text": "to build documentation ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10236/?time=72"
  },
  {
    "text": "for your Swift frameworks, libraries, and packages. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10236/?time=74"
  },
  {
    "text": "You can start using it right away ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10236/?time=78"
  },
  {
    "text": "without any setup ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10236/?time=80"
  },
  {
    "text": "and then expand your documentation ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10236/?time=81"
  },
  {
    "text": "with additional material over time. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10236/?time=83"
  },
  {
    "text": "And it's just as easy ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10236/?time=87"
  },
  {
    "text": "to export your documentation ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10236/?time=89"
  },
  {
    "text": "from the Developer Documentation window.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10236/?time=90"
  },
  {
    "text": "You can share the exported documentation ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10236/?time=94"
  },
  {
    "text": "archive with others ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10236/?time=96"
  },
  {
    "text": "so that they can import and read the documentation in Xcode, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10236/?time=97"
  },
  {
    "text": "or you can host the documentation archive online. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10236/?time=101"
  },
  {
    "text": "If you want to learn more about documentation in Xcode ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10236/?time=106"
  },
  {
    "text": "and about authoring documentation for your symbols, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10236/?time=109"
  },
  {
    "text": "my colleagues Victoria and Ethan ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10236/?time=112"
  },
  {
    "text": "talk about just that in the ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10236/?time=114"
  },
  {
    "text": "\"Meet DocC documentation in Xcode\" session. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10236/?time=116"
  },
  {
    "text": "In the second half of this presentation, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10236/?time=121"
  },
  {
    "text": "I'll talk about how you can automate building documentation ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10236/?time=123"
  },
  {
    "text": "on the command line. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10236/?time=126"
  },
  {
    "text": "But for now, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10236/?time=127"
  },
  {
    "text": "I'll use the documentation archive ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10236/?time=128"
  },
  {
    "text": "that I exported from Xcode to host on our server.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10236/?time=130"
  },
  {
    "text": "The documentation archive itself is a container ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10236/?time=135"
  },
  {
    "text": "that holds all the data ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10236/?time=138"
  },
  {
    "text": "to both read the documentation in Xcode ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10236/?time=139"
  },
  {
    "text": "and to host it online.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10236/?time=142"
  },
  {
    "text": "It is structured as a single page ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10236/?time=145"
  },
  {
    "text": "Vue.js web app ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10236/?time=148"
  },
  {
    "text": "that's used to render ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10236/?time=149"
  },
  {
    "text": "both your reference documentation and articles ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10236/?time=150"
  },
  {
    "text": "and your rich and interactive tutorials.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10236/?time=153"
  },
  {
    "text": "There are two different types of requests ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10236/?time=158"
  },
  {
    "text": "that the server needs to handle ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10236/?time=160"
  },
  {
    "text": "to host the documentation archive. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10236/?time=161"
  },
  {
    "text": "Requests for documentation and tutorial pages ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10236/?time=164"
  },
  {
    "text": "where the request URL starts with ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10236/?time=167"
  },
  {
    "text": "/documentation/ or /tutorials/ ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10236/?time=170"
  },
  {
    "text": "and requests for additional files and data ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10236/?time=174"
  },
  {
    "text": "that is loaded by the web app, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10236/?time=177"
  },
  {
    "text": "where the request URL matches the relative file path ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10236/?time=179"
  },
  {
    "text": "for one of the files in the documentation archive.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10236/?time=182"
  },
  {
    "text": "Let's look at an example of the requests ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10236/?time=186"
  },
  {
    "text": "that make up a page ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10236/?time=188"
  },
  {
    "text": "and how the server should respond to them.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10236/?time=190"
  },
  {
    "text": "When a developer goes to read your hosted documentation ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10236/?time=194"
  },
  {
    "text": "and the browser requests a page, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10236/?time=197"
  },
  {
    "text": "if the request starts with /documentation/ or /tutorials/ ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10236/?time=200"
  },
  {
    "text": "then the server should respond with the index.html file ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10236/?time=205"
  },
  {
    "text": "that's located in the documentation archive. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10236/?time=208"
  },
  {
    "text": "That file references CSS and JavaScript ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10236/?time=212"
  },
  {
    "text": "within the documentation archive, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10236/?time=215"
  },
  {
    "text": "which the browser requests to load the rest of the web app.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10236/?time=217"
  },
  {
    "text": "Once that is loaded, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10236/?time=223"
  },
  {
    "text": "the web app requests the content for that page ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10236/?time=224"
  },
  {
    "text": "and any images or other media that it references.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10236/?time=227"
  },
  {
    "text": "Both the files ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10236/?time=232"
  },
  {
    "text": "that is referenced by the index.html file ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10236/?time=234"
  },
  {
    "text": "and the content and media that is loaded by the web app ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10236/?time=236"
  },
  {
    "text": "use request URLs that match the folder structure ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10236/?time=239"
  },
  {
    "text": "of the documentation archive.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10236/?time=242"
  },
  {
    "text": "Now that you've seen how the hosting server ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10236/?time=246"
  },
  {
    "text": "needs to respond to incoming requests, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10236/?time=248"
  },
  {
    "text": "let's look at that in a demo. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10236/?time=250"
  },
  {
    "text": "Many of you may already have a server ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10236/?time=253"
  },
  {
    "text": "that hosts your website. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10236/?time=254"
  },
  {
    "text": "For our project, we're using an Apache server, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10236/?time=256"
  },
  {
    "text": "but you can use any server that allows for custom routing. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10236/?time=259"
  },
  {
    "text": "This is our website about SlothCreator. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10236/?time=263"
  },
  {
    "text": "We've added this \"Read Documentation\" button ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10236/?time=266"
  },
  {
    "text": "below the introductory text in the center of the page, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10236/?time=268"
  },
  {
    "text": "but the button doesn't work just yet. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10236/?time=271"
  },
  {
    "text": "So let's fix that. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10236/?time=273"
  },
  {
    "text": "I've already copied the documentation archive ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10236/?time=276"
  },
  {
    "text": "into the directory where we're hosting our website ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10236/?time=278"
  },
  {
    "text": "and added an empty .htaccess file. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10236/?time=280"
  },
  {
    "text": "But I haven't set up any of the routing in it.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10236/?time=283"
  },
  {
    "text": "There are two routing rules that I need to add: ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10236/?time=289"
  },
  {
    "text": "one for the documentation and tutorial pages ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10236/?time=292"
  },
  {
    "text": "and one for the additional files and data. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10236/?time=295"
  },
  {
    "text": "For the first rule, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10236/?time=299"
  },
  {
    "text": "the pattern that I want to match ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10236/?time=301"
  },
  {
    "text": "is any URL that starts with \"documentation\" or \"tutorials\" ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10236/?time=303"
  },
  {
    "text": "as its first path component. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10236/?time=307"
  },
  {
    "text": "Any request that matches this pattern, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10236/?time=310"
  },
  {
    "text": "I want to reroute to the index.html file ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10236/?time=313"
  },
  {
    "text": "within the documentation archive. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10236/?time=316"
  },
  {
    "text": "Lastly, I'll end the rule with a flag ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10236/?time=319"
  },
  {
    "text": "to stop evaluating rules ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10236/?time=322"
  },
  {
    "text": "if the request matches this rule. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10236/?time=323"
  },
  {
    "text": "For the second rule, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10236/?time=327"
  },
  {
    "text": "I'm going to be more explicit about the pattern. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10236/?time=328"
  },
  {
    "text": "Since we're also hosting our website with this server, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10236/?time=331"
  },
  {
    "text": "we don't want to reroute requests ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10236/?time=334"
  },
  {
    "text": "for the website to files in the documentation archive.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10236/?time=335"
  },
  {
    "text": "If I look inside of the documentation archive, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10236/?time=342"
  },
  {
    "text": "you can see that there are a handful ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10236/?time=346"
  },
  {
    "text": "of top-level files and folders ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10236/?time=347"
  },
  {
    "text": "that I can match in a pattern. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10236/?time=349"
  },
  {
    "text": "So I'll add a pattern that matches all of those.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10236/?time=351"
  },
  {
    "text": "In this case, the request URL ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10236/?time=357"
  },
  {
    "text": "is a relative file path for one of the files ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10236/?time=360"
  },
  {
    "text": "in the documentation archive, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10236/?time=362"
  },
  {
    "text": "so I'll reroute the request to the matched pattern ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10236/?time=364"
  },
  {
    "text": "but prefixed with SlothCreator.doccarchive. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10236/?time=367"
  },
  {
    "text": "And just like before, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10236/?time=371"
  },
  {
    "text": "I added the same flag to stop evaluating rules. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10236/?time=373"
  },
  {
    "text": "Now, if I reload the webpage ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10236/?time=377"
  },
  {
    "text": "and click on the documentation link, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10236/?time=379"
  },
  {
    "text": "you'll see that the server now hosts ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10236/?time=382"
  },
  {
    "text": "both our website and our documentation.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10236/?time=384"
  },
  {
    "text": "The main SlothCreator page ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10236/?time=389"
  },
  {
    "text": "groups important symbols into topics ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10236/?time=390"
  },
  {
    "text": "related to higher level tasks.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10236/?time=393"
  },
  {
    "text": "And each of those group related symbols ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10236/?time=399"
  },
  {
    "text": "into more specific topics.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10236/?time=401"
  },
  {
    "text": "DocC comes with a built-in, clean design ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10236/?time=410"
  },
  {
    "text": "that's made to fit in well with a variety of projects. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10236/?time=414"
  },
  {
    "text": "This makes it really easy to have good-looking, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10236/?time=417"
  },
  {
    "text": "elegant documentation for your projects, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10236/?time=420"
  },
  {
    "text": "like our SlothCreator documentation here. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10236/?time=422"
  },
  {
    "text": "Now that we host a copy of our documentation ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10236/?time=426"
  },
  {
    "text": "on our website, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10236/?time=428"
  },
  {
    "text": "let's look at how to automate ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10236/?time=430"
  },
  {
    "text": "building and updating the documentation archive. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10236/?time=431"
  },
  {
    "text": "To do that, I'm going to write a script ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10236/?time=435"
  },
  {
    "text": "that calls xcodebuild. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10236/?time=437"
  },
  {
    "text": "Once I have a script that does this, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10236/?time=439"
  },
  {
    "text": "I can run it whenever new changes are made ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10236/?time=441"
  },
  {
    "text": "so that the hosted documentation ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10236/?time=443"
  },
  {
    "text": "is always up to date. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10236/?time=445"
  },
  {
    "text": "New in Xcode 13, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10236/?time=448"
  },
  {
    "text": "you can build documentation on the command line ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10236/?time=450"
  },
  {
    "text": "with xcodebuild's new docbuild action. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10236/?time=453"
  },
  {
    "text": "When you build documentation in Xcode or xcodebuild, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10236/?time=457"
  },
  {
    "text": "it works like a standard build ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10236/?time=461"
  },
  {
    "text": "that also builds documentation.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10236/?time=463"
  },
  {
    "text": "During the build, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10236/?time=467"
  },
  {
    "text": "the Swift compiler gathers detailed information ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10236/?time=468"
  },
  {
    "text": "about all the public symbols, their relationships, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10236/?time=471"
  },
  {
    "text": "and in-source documentation comments ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10236/?time=474"
  },
  {
    "text": "and passes this as a file called a symbol graph ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10236/?time=477"
  },
  {
    "text": "to the documentation compiler ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10236/?time=480"
  },
  {
    "text": "to produce a documentation archive ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10236/?time=482"
  },
  {
    "text": "with all the necessary data ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10236/?time=484"
  },
  {
    "text": "to both read the documentation in Xcode ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10236/?time=486"
  },
  {
    "text": "and to host it online. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10236/?time=489"
  },
  {
    "text": "If the target has an associated documentation catalog ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10236/?time=491"
  },
  {
    "text": "with additional articles, media, or tutorials for your project, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10236/?time=494"
  },
  {
    "text": "then the documentation compiler ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10236/?time=499"
  },
  {
    "text": "is going to combine all of that content ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10236/?time=501"
  },
  {
    "text": "with the symbol information ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10236/?time=503"
  },
  {
    "text": "when it produces the documentation archive.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10236/?time=504"
  },
  {
    "text": "If you want to learn more ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10236/?time=508"
  },
  {
    "text": "about documentation catalogs, check out ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10236/?time=510"
  },
  {
    "text": "the \"Elevate your DocC documentation in Xcode\" session ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10236/?time=512"
  },
  {
    "text": "where my colleagues Bea and Jack ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10236/?time=516"
  },
  {
    "text": "talk about the different types of documentation ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10236/?time=518"
  },
  {
    "text": "and how you can leverage each of them ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10236/?time=521"
  },
  {
    "text": "to offer developers a great way ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10236/?time=522"
  },
  {
    "text": "for learning about your project.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10236/?time=524"
  },
  {
    "text": "Building documentation doesn't just apply to your targets. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10236/?time=528"
  },
  {
    "text": "If your target has dependencies to other Swift frameworks, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10236/?time=532"
  },
  {
    "text": "libraries, or packages, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10236/?time=535"
  },
  {
    "text": "then the same process is applied to all of those as well ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10236/?time=537"
  },
  {
    "text": "so that you get all the relevant documentation for your project ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10236/?time=541"
  },
  {
    "text": "all in one place. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10236/?time=544"
  },
  {
    "text": "Since I'm looking to automate building and updating ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10236/?time=547"
  },
  {
    "text": "our hosted documentation with a script, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10236/?time=550"
  },
  {
    "text": "xcodebuild on the command line ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10236/?time=552"
  },
  {
    "text": "is going to be perfect for that.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10236/?time=554"
  },
  {
    "text": "The new docbuild action in xcodebuild ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10236/?time=558"
  },
  {
    "text": "works just like the default build action, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10236/?time=561"
  },
  {
    "text": "but it also builds documentation.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10236/?time=563"
  },
  {
    "text": "Like the build action, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10236/?time=567"
  },
  {
    "text": "you pass it the scheme that you want to build ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10236/?time=569"
  },
  {
    "text": "and the project or workspace that it's a part of. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10236/?time=571"
  },
  {
    "text": "You can also call xcodebuild ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10236/?time=575"
  },
  {
    "text": "from within the directory that contains your project, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10236/?time=577"
  },
  {
    "text": "workspace, or Swift package ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10236/?time=580"
  },
  {
    "text": "and only pass it the scheme. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10236/?time=582"
  },
  {
    "text": "Depending on your project and scheme, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10236/?time=584"
  },
  {
    "text": "you may want to pass other flags ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10236/?time=586"
  },
  {
    "text": "such as sdk, destination, or configuration ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10236/?time=588"
  },
  {
    "text": "to customize how your project is built.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10236/?time=591"
  },
  {
    "text": "It's not required to do so. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10236/?time=595"
  },
  {
    "text": "But to make it more easy to follow, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10236/?time=597"
  },
  {
    "text": "I'll specify a custom derivedDataPath, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10236/?time=599"
  },
  {
    "text": "where the build products and the built documentation ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10236/?time=602"
  },
  {
    "text": "will be written. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10236/?time=605"
  },
  {
    "text": "After the build has completed, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10236/?time=607"
  },
  {
    "text": "I can find all of the built documentation archives ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10236/?time=609"
  },
  {
    "text": "using the .doccarchive file extension ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10236/?time=612"
  },
  {
    "text": "and copy each of them ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10236/?time=616"
  },
  {
    "text": "to another location or to another machine.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10236/?time=617"
  },
  {
    "text": "Let's take a look at that in a demo.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10236/?time=621"
  },
  {
    "text": "This is our hosted documentation from before. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10236/?time=625"
  },
  {
    "text": "It groups related symbols into topics ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10236/?time=628"
  },
  {
    "text": "so that it's easy for developers ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10236/?time=630"
  },
  {
    "text": "to find the core types for a specific task.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10236/?time=632"
  },
  {
    "text": "In the time since we built this version, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10236/?time=638"
  },
  {
    "text": "my colleagues have added some new articles ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10236/?time=640"
  },
  {
    "text": "and tutorials that appear in the Essentials section. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10236/?time=642"
  },
  {
    "text": "So now is a great time for me to write that automation script ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10236/?time=645"
  },
  {
    "text": "that builds the latest documentation ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10236/?time=649"
  },
  {
    "text": "and updates our website.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10236/?time=650"
  },
  {
    "text": "Like you just saw, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10236/?time=654"
  },
  {
    "text": "we build documentation ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10236/?time=655"
  },
  {
    "text": "by calling xcodebuild's docbuild action ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10236/?time=657"
  },
  {
    "text": "and update our website by finding and copying ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10236/?time=661"
  },
  {
    "text": "the documentation archive into the directory ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10236/?time=664"
  },
  {
    "text": "where we're hosting our website from.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10236/?time=666"
  },
  {
    "text": "I already know what scheme I need to pass ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10236/?time=671"
  },
  {
    "text": "because it's the same as I see in the scheme selector in Xcode. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10236/?time=674"
  },
  {
    "text": "If I didn't already have Xcode open, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10236/?time=678"
  },
  {
    "text": "I could also run xcodebuild -list ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10236/?time=681"
  },
  {
    "text": "on the command line to list all of the available schemes.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10236/?time=684"
  },
  {
    "text": "Again, the custom derivedDataPath ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10236/?time=689"
  },
  {
    "text": "is not required, but it makes it easier to follow ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10236/?time=692"
  },
  {
    "text": "where the built documentation is written and found.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10236/?time=694"
  },
  {
    "text": "After the build has completed, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10236/?time=702"
  },
  {
    "text": "I can find all of the documentation archives ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10236/?time=704"
  },
  {
    "text": "and copy each of them into the directory ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10236/?time=706"
  },
  {
    "text": "where we're hosting our website from. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10236/?time=708"
  },
  {
    "text": "And with that done, I'm ready to run the script.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10236/?time=712"
  },
  {
    "text": "Now, if I refresh, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10236/?time=722"
  },
  {
    "text": "you can see the added article and tutorial ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10236/?time=724"
  },
  {
    "text": "in the Essentials section. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10236/?time=726"
  },
  {
    "text": "With these latest changes, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10236/?time=729"
  },
  {
    "text": "our documentation looks more complete. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10236/?time=731"
  },
  {
    "text": "And people who are new to SlothCreator ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10236/?time=733"
  },
  {
    "text": "have a great place to get started, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10236/?time=735"
  },
  {
    "text": "whether they prefer the content of an article ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10236/?time=737"
  },
  {
    "text": "or the step-by-step instructions in one of our tutorials.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10236/?time=745"
  },
  {
    "text": "Now, updating our hosted documentation ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10236/?time=755"
  },
  {
    "text": "is as easy as running a script. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10236/?time=757"
  },
  {
    "text": "And if we run it as part of a post-merge hook ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10236/?time=760"
  },
  {
    "text": "on our continuous integration server, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10236/?time=763"
  },
  {
    "text": "then we can ensure that our hosted documentation ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10236/?time=765"
  },
  {
    "text": "always stays up to date.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10236/?time=767"
  },
  {
    "text": "To recap what we talked about in this session, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10236/?time=771"
  },
  {
    "text": "you can share documentation archives ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10236/?time=775"
  },
  {
    "text": "or host them online ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10236/?time=777"
  },
  {
    "text": "to give a great documentation experience ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10236/?time=778"
  },
  {
    "text": "to consumers of your framework, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10236/?time=780"
  },
  {
    "text": "even before they've started using it in Xcode. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10236/?time=782"
  },
  {
    "text": "And building documentation on the command line ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10236/?time=785"
  },
  {
    "text": "allows you to include documentation ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10236/?time=788"
  },
  {
    "text": "in your automation workflows. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10236/?time=790"
  },
  {
    "text": "If you want to learn more about DocC documentation, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10236/?time=793"
  },
  {
    "text": "\"Meet DocC documentation in Xcode\" ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10236/?time=797"
  },
  {
    "text": "is a fantastic introduction ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10236/?time=799"
  },
  {
    "text": "to the new documentation features in Xcode. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10236/?time=801"
  },
  {
    "text": "\"Elevate your DocC documentation in Xcode\" ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10236/?time=805"
  },
  {
    "text": "goes deep into how you can enhance ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10236/?time=808"
  },
  {
    "text": "your documentation with DocC catalogs. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10236/?time=810"
  },
  {
    "text": "And \"Build interactive tutorials using DocC\" ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10236/?time=813"
  },
  {
    "text": "details how you can structure your ideas ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10236/?time=817"
  },
  {
    "text": "and create amazing tutorials for your project. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10236/?time=819"
  },
  {
    "text": "Thank you for watching. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10236/?time=823"
  },
  {
    "text": "[music]",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10236/?time=824"
  }
]